), Zarubezhny Golos (The Voice of Exile), Ob'yedinyenie (Union) and Klich (The Clarion), bought the latest numbers of émigré magazines and — for comparison — several Soviet magazines and newspapers. It was decided that every day after dinner they would read to one another aloud. Noticing that some newspapers printed a chess section, she wondered at first whether to cut out and destroy these bits, but she feared by this to insult Luzhin.

